        "created_at": "2022-12-24T00:07:43.906Z",
        "cooked": "<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=4521761&amp;iNote=10210709\"><b>1976 Hospices de Beaune Meursault 1er Cru Charmes Cuv\u00e9e Albert Grivault</b></a> - France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Meursault 1er Cru (12/21/2022)<br>\nThis was nothing short of spectacular. It was a little lean and dry to begin with, but stacked on mid-palate pud with air. There were notes of toast, custard apple, almond butter and lavender. Each sip unlocked a new subtle nuance and despite the relatively low acidity of the wine it was fresh, precise and long.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a></p>",
